-------> Scripture (20min)

Before picking up where we left off I want to do a quick review of chapter 5 verses 13-16 that we covered last week

We are in Chapter 5 of a book called Matthew. Matthew was an outcast jew and former tax collector who followed Jesus and became one of his 12 apostles

We are working through what is perhaps the most famous sermon ever given. Sermon on the mount, given by Jesus

Jesus begins the sermon with the beatitudes which outline Kingdom character. The beatitudes describe the character of those who flourish in Gods eyes

Last week we covered Kingdom identity in verses 13-16 where Jesus calls his disciples salt and light

The salt that preserves goodness and defends against decay and the light that shines so those in darkness might see it and approach it

Now, in verses 17-20 which we cover today, Jesus is anchoring his people in Gods word

---> Read chapter 5 verses 17-20

Let's define some terms and build a bit of context so we can understand these words in the correct frame

The Law or prophets refers to the Old Testament writing. The word of God

During the time of Jesus, there was no new testament, only the old testament.

The law and the prophets refers to scripture which at the time was Genesis to Malachi








The word of God. The laws of God. This is the foundation. The bedrock

Not an iota. A single dot. From the OT 

The religious elite have perverted and twisted the word of God. They have manipulated scripture. Teaching bad doctrine. 

Don’t think for a second that I’ve come to abolish the OT. I have come to fulfill it

When Jesus was alive, there was no NT

Jesus says I came to fulfill it. To affirm it. To raise the bar on everyone

The entire OT is a prophecy about Christ. It all predicts Christ. The OT points to Christ. Christ is the embodiement of the OT. He is the fulfilment of the OT. He is the fulfilment of the moral law. A man who did not sin. A man who lived fully in alignment with his fathers words

Jesus is everywhere in the OT. The OT is speaking about Jesus. 

Jesus is saying that every chapter, verse, letter and even iota was intentionally put there by God. It’s all relevant. 

He’s saying you must pay deep attention to every word, every iota of the word of God. I’m not here to replace it, I’m here to fulfill it. To embody it. To BE it. 

The truth of God word is eternal. It outlines everything. It’s our heavenly father’s love letter to his children. Written by God through 40 men on 3 different continents, 3 different languages over 1500 years. A unity of cohesive thought is not by chance. It’s not random. It’s divine truth by God through messengers that are men

Bad doctrine is only possible because people aren’t reading Gods word. Aren’t reading the source material

19: if you tone down the word you will be called least in the Kingdom. If anyone waters down the laws. Dilutes them for fear of hurting feelings. For fear of judgement. In order to blend with culture. You will be called least in the Kingdom

Those who tell the truth. Who uphold the fidelity of the word. Every iota. Straight truth. Will be called great in the kingdom of heaven

Don’t relax the word. Don’t dilute it. Don’t be pressured by worldly opinions. Be true Christians. Be true to the word

Know it. Share it. Call others to know it and abide by it

20: religious elite of the day. People looked up to them. They were righteousness role models. They were relaxing and perverting Gods laws. They were creating their own laws and calling them Gods laws. Man made traditions and laws being labelled Gods laws. 

The antidote to Bad teachings and bad doctrines is people reading the word. Don’t outsource knowledge of Gods word to others. Accept the responsibility to know the word by studying it. 






Now Jesus shares kingdom laws and sets the record straight on the manipulation and perversion of God's laws that were happening at the time

